The paper deals with the development of a deep convolutional neural network model for generating radiomic images efficiently. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper also deals with the computation and visualization of textural information present in radiological images, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
